The President welcomes the signing of a cessation of hostilities agreement in South Sudan and calls for its full and immediate implementation. He urges South Sudan's leaders to engage in an inclusive political dialogue to address the root causes of the conflict. The participation of political detainees is crucial, and efforts will be made to expedite their release. The President appreciates the role played by regional partners in advancing these efforts. The United States has long supported the independence, peace, and prosperity of South Sudan. To regain trust, South Sudan's leaders must demonstrate a commitment to a peaceful resolution and ensure accountability for those who have committed atrocities. The United States remains a steadfast partner in promoting a more peaceful and unified South Sudan.